![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

There's a potential division-by-zero error here if `rootSize` is `0`. This can happen if the user clears the 'Root Font Size' input or enters `0`, which will cause 'Infinity' to be displayed in the `rem` and `em` fields. You should add a guard to prevent division by zero, and clear the other fields if the input is invalid.

```suggestion
        if (!isNaN(num) && rootSize > 0) {
            setRem((num / rootSize).toString())
            setEm((num / rootSize).toString())
        } else {
            setRem("")
            setEm("")
        }
```

