![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The `navigator.clipboard.writeText` API is not available in all browsers or in insecure contexts (non-HTTPS, except for localhost). It's good practice to check for its availability before using it. Additionally, `writeText` returns a Promise, which you can use to handle potential errors and provide feedback to the user (e.g., showing a 'Copied!' message).

```
    const copyToClipboard = async (text: string) => {
        if (!navigator.clipboard) {
            console.error("Clipboard API not available.");
            return;
        }
        try {
            await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
            // Optionally, show a success message to the user
        } catch (err) {
            console.error("Failed to copy text: ", err);
            // Optionally, show an error message to the user
        }
    }
```
